.Dd 04/17/2023
.Dt SIMPLE_SHELL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm simple_shell
.Nd A lightweight UNIX-style command interpreter written in C

.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op command

.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
program is a minimal UNIX command interpreter that executes basic shell commands.
It was originally developed as part of the Holberton School low-level programming curriculum and later migrated for continued learning and portfolio development.

The shell provides an interactive command prompt allowing users to enter executable commands or scripts.

.Sh FEATURES
.Bl -bullet
.It Execute basic shell commands (e.g. ls, pwd, echo)
.It Command path resolution
.It Basic built-in commands
.It Command history navigation (limited)
.It Semicolon command chaining
.It Error handling and exit status reporting
.El

.Sh LIMITATIONS
This shell is a learning project and does not implement full POSIX shell functionality.

Unsupported features include:
.Bl -bullet
.It Pipes (|)
.It Redirection (> < <<)
.It Background execution (&)
.It Aliases
.It Advanced environment variable expansion
.It Job control
.El

Behavior may vary for complex arguments or special characters.  
The program is not intended for production environments and has not undergone full stress or security testing.

.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
Successful completion
.It >0
An error occurred
.El

.Sh EXAMPLES
Run the shell:
.Bd -literal
./simple_shell
.Ed

Run commands:
.Bd -literal
ls -l
cd /path/to/dir
./script.sh
.Ed

.Sh CONTROLS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It CTRL-D
Exit shell
.It CTRL-C
Interrupt current process
.It Up / Down arrows
Navigate command history (limited)
.El

.Sh AUTHORS
.An Joshua Riggs
and
.An Ashly Riggs

.Sh NOTES
Migrated from academic repository to professional development account for ongoing enhancement and documentation.
